## the beauty

間

        Why does topology prove algebra?
        
        A polynomial is a continuous map ℂ → ℂ.
        If it avoids zero, it maps to ℂ\{0}.
        ℂ\{0} ≃ S¹ × ℝ (homotopy equivalent to circle).
        
        The fundamental group detects winding.
        Winding is homotopy invariant.
        Large circles wind n times (algebra).
        Small circles wind 0 times (topology).
        
        The polynomial cannot smoothly transition.
        Something must break.
        That break is a root.
        
        ◊

